{"author":{"id":"977fec8a59c245f25e0e700fa290ef50836c624572869487e9e47fedc85061ee"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1459958984,"nonce":"hS/SU5shoQzSdyxM+mjPZ5nKQSk=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDIwNjQ0NDY4OA==","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/716#issuecomment-206444688"},"message":"\u003e I know this is a larger issues, but it would be great to expose those things hosted on galaxydepot somewhere and show how they are built\n\ngalaxydepot (for the most part) is just a mirror, in case the original source download goes away. A few big packages (R for example) are also hosted as binary versions, so admins don't spend hours compiling these. Everyone can get things into galaxydepot, the procedure is outlined here:\nhttps://github.com/galaxyproject/cargo-port under contributions.\n\nI do agree with your general notion, nowadays you need to know a lot of different things and details to understand exactly where a dependency is coming from. Add to that conda and docker, and the confusion is complete. I guess we would need to find a way to expose this information more clearly in the toolshed or the \"manage installed tools\" admin section.","files":null}]}